		"name": "High-Scale Energy Ingestion Engine",
		"description": "## Overview\n\nThis service ingests two independent telemetry streams every 60 seconds:\n\n- Smart Meter stream (AC energy consumption)\n    \n- Vehicle stream (DC energy delivered + SoC + temperature)\n    \n\nIt stores data using a hot/cold strategy to support:\n\n- high write throughput\n    \n- fast current-state queries\n    \n- fast 24-hour analytics without full table scans\n    \n\n## Data Strategy\n\n### Cold Store (History)\n\nAppend-only telemetry:\n\n- meter_telemetry\n    \n- vehicle_telemetry\n    \n\n### Hot Store (Operational)\n\nUpserted latest state:\n\n- meter_live_status\n    \n- vehicle_live_status\n    \n\n## Insert vs Upsert\n\n- History path uses INSERT (append-only audit trail)\n    \n- Live path uses UPSERT to keep one row per device\n    \n\n## Analytics Query Performance\n\nAnalytics uses indexed time-window queries:\n\n- vehicle_telemetry(vehicle_id, ts)\n    \n- meter_telemetry(meter_id, ts)\n    \n\nThis prevents full scans on historical tables.",
